HEADWORD: brisling
<hw>brisling</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>a small fatty European
fish; usually smoked or canned.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sprat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a small herring (<spn>Clupea sprattus</spn>)
processed like a sardine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> sprat.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

